The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and their structures, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of multicut and backdoor set detection techniques suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also deals with graph connectivity and cycle problems, which suggests category cs.GT (Graph Theory).
